# Project: Windows ME Resume

Interactive resume styled as a Windows Millennium Edition desktop. Deployed to GitHub Pages at `p0rt.github.io/resume/`.

## Tech Stack

- React 19 + TypeScript 6 + Vite 8
- `98.css` library for Win98/ME base styling
- Single global CSS (`src/global.css`) with BEM-like naming on top of 98.css
- No CSS modules, no CSS-in-JS, no Tailwind
- No state management library — `useState`, `useCallback`, `useRef` only
- GitHub Actions CI → `tsc -b && vite build` → gh-pages

## Architecture

```
src/
  App.tsx              — root: window manager, global state, context menu
  types.ts             — WindowId union type, WindowState interface
  global.css           — all styles (overrides 98.css)
  hooks/
    useWindowManager.ts — open/close/minimize/maximize/focus/move windows
  components/
    Desktop.tsx        — draggable icons, right-click context menu
    Window.tsx         — window chrome (title bar, drag, min/max/close)
    Taskbar.tsx        — start menu, running windows, clock
    Notepad.tsx        — resume.txt content
    Explorer.tsx       — My Computer + Experience views
    Browser.tsx        — IE5 simulator: page/iframe modes, history
    PhotoViewer.tsx    — avatar display
    ContextMenu.tsx    — right-click menu with submenus
    Icons.tsx          — SVG icon components
```

## Key Conventions

- Named exports only (no default exports)
- `import type { ... }` for type-only imports
- Props interfaces defined locally in component files (not exported), except shared types like `MenuItem`
- All handler callbacks wrapped in `useCallback`
- Data (resume text, job history, links) hardcoded in components
- Vite base URL: `/resume/`
